President Obama and German Chancellor Angela Merkel spoke on the phone to discuss the financial situation in the eurozone. They expressed gratitude for the recent agreement on a new rescue program for Greece to reduce its debt. They also acknowledged that the EU fiscal pact, actions by the European Central Bank, and reforms by Spain and Italy have been positive steps in addressing the eurozone crisis. The leaders also talked about the upcoming G-8 Summit and agreed that the focus should be on promoting growth and creating jobs.